&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Midwife Antenatal Clinic – Preterm Birth Midwife &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for dynamic enthusiastic Band 6 Midwife to join our team within the Antenatal clinic at Buckinghamshire NHS Trust. This role will have a focus on Preterm Pregnancy and woman’s care pathways.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicants will be motivated, passionate and dedicated to providing high quality women-centred care in line with the national agenda. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will work collaboratively within our multidisciplinary team supporting woman and their families though their pregnancy journey.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your experience will ensure that you provide a high standard of care to our mothers and their families. As a member of our team you will be professional, reliable, safe and compassionate and have excellent communication skills and a progressive attitude to the continual improvement of patient care through evidence based practice. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Hours will be based mainly at Stoke Mandeville Hospital but may require some cross site working. The Service is open between 8-6 pm Monday – Friday and the successful applicant will undertake a variety of shifts between these opening times to ensure the clinics are covered. Minimum of 22.5 hours required &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is recruited on a rotational basis which may require the post holder to work in all areas of maternity and cover all shifts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information relating to this role please contact Alison Mckillop (Antenatal Clinic Sister ) Email: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alison.Mckillop@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron Elaine Gilbert email : &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Elaine.Gilbert2@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
